== Preverbs
Sometimes we want to talk not only about the activity itself, but about how we
relate to it. Maybe we #emph[want to] do something. Maybe we #emph[can] do
something. Maybe we #emph[start] or #emph[keep on] doing something.

In English, these are known as #emph[auxilliary and modal verbs]. Toki Pona has
a similar system, we like to call them #emph[preverbs]! A preverb is an added
verb that goes before the main verb. You already know some of them! Let\'s learn
what they mean when they act as preverbs:

#list((
  word("ůĪ§Ė", "kama", "to begin to ..., to become ..."),
  word("ůĪ§ą", "awen", "to continue to ..., to still ..."),
))

Only a few verbs in Toki Pona are allowed to be preverbs. So let\'s also learn
the remaining ones.

#list((
  word("ůĪ•∑", "wile", "to want to ...; to want, to require"),
  word("ůĪ§ė", "ken", "to be able to ...; to allow, to be possible"),
  word("ůĪ§É", "alasa", "to try to ...; to seek, to hunt, to gather"),
))

Just like #strong[ůĪ§Ė kama] and #strong[ůĪ§ą awen], they can be both preverbs and
normal verbs!

Preverbs are very versatile! Let\'s look at some phrases with preverbs:

#list((
  word("ůĪ•∑ůĪ§Ę", "wile lape", "to want to sleep"),
  word("ůĪ§ąůĪ•Ē", "awen pona", "to continue to be good"),
  word("ůĪ§ĖůĪ•°", "kama sona", "to become knowledgeable, to learn"),
  word("ůĪ§ÉůĪ§ĖůĪ•Ķ", "alasa kama wawa", "to try to become strong"),
))

